COMPILING SHM DISTANCE FUNCTION - LINUX
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
gcc -c -fPIC SHMDistance.c -o SHMDistance.o
gcc -shared -Wl,-soname,SHMDistance.so -o SHMDistance.so SHMDistance.o 


COMPILING SHM DISTANCE FUNCTION - OS X
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
gcc -c -fPIC SHMDistance.c -o SHMDistance.o
gcc -shared -Wl,-dylib_install_name,SHMDistance.so -o SHMDistance.so SHMDistance.o 


INSTALL - LINUX
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1) The simplest way to install all Python dependencies is to install the full 
   SciPy stack using the instructions at http://scipy.org/install.html. Then 
   install Biopython according to the instructions at 
   http://biopython.org/DIST/docs/install/Installation.html. And install rpy2
   according to the instructions at http://rpy.sourceforge.net. R can typically
   be installed using the package management features of your distribution.

2) Unzip the Change-O bundle and copy all files into the same directory. Add 
   that directory to your $PATH.


INSTALL - WINDOWS
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1) Install Python 2.7.5+ from http://python.org/download.

2) Install R from http://www.r-project.org

2) Install NumPy, SciPy, pandas, Biopython and rpy2 using the packages 
   available from http://www.lfd.uci.edu/~gohlke/pythonlibs.

3) Unzip the Change-O bundle and copy all files into the same directory. Add 
   that directory to your %Path%.  On Windows 7 the %Path% setting is located 
   under 'Control Panel' -> 'System and Security' -> 'System' -> 
   'Advanced System Settings' -> 'Environment variables' -> 'System variables' 
   -> 'Path'

4) The Change-O scripts should then be directly executable from the Command Prompt.
   If not, correct the file association for .py files by right-clicking on a .py
   file, selecting 'Open with' -> 'Choose default program...', choosing the 
   python.exe from Python 2.7, and checking 'Always use the selected program'.
   

INSTALL - OS X
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1) Install Xcode 3.2.6
   Available from the Apple store or http://developer.apple.com/downloads.
   If you have a newer version (eg, Xcode 4.6.3) that will work also,
   but Xcode 3 is free of charge.  If Xcode fails to install with an
   "Unknown Error", change the date on your system to some time in 2011,
   install Xcode, and then change the date back to the proper setting.

2) Install XQuartz 2.7.5
   Available from http://xquartz.macosforge.org/landing

3) Install Homebrew
   Follow the installation and post-installation instructions on http://brew.sh

4) Open a terminal and install gfortran (required for SciPy) using Homebrew:
   > brew install gfortran
   If this fails instead run:
   > brew install --env=std gfortran
   (This can take an hour to install.)

5) Install Python 2.7.5+ and set it as the default python executable
   > brew install python
   > echo 'export PATH=/usr/local/bin:$PATH' >> ~/.profile
   Exit and reopen the terminal application so the PATH setting takes effect

6) Install NumPy, SciPy, pandas, Biopython and rpy2 using the Python package
   manager:
   > pip install numpy
   > pip install scipy
   > pip install pandas
   > pip install biopython
   > pip install rpy2

7) Add the Change-O/pRESTO installation to your PATH setting. For example,
   if you copied the tools into /Users/Username/changeo, then set:
   > echo 'export PATH=$HOME/changeo:$PATH' >> ~/.profile
   Exit and reopen the terminal application so the PATH setting takes effect
   